The police's Malcolm Pojie says following an investigation, the remains were found on a field near a high school in the area. CAPE TOWN - A skull has been found on a pavement in front of a house in Conville, George. Authorities suspect the skull was dragged there by dogs on Sunday. The police's Malcolm Pojie says following an investigation, the remains were found on a field near a high school in the area. “We have opened an inquest docket for further investigation. An autopsy will be conducted during the week to determine the exact cause of death; and perhaps the age and for how the body has been in the field,” he said. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)